    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>James Wheaton was a farmer and cooper of Pomfret, Connecticut.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">James Wheaton Daybooks</emph> consists of 2 volumes, one covering the years 1796-1840 and the other 1816-1873 (84 and 258 pp. respectively).  Contents include records of funds received by his sons Royal and Childs Wheaton toward their portions of their father's estate, 1801-1817; records of the servicing of bulls, and of calves born, 1853-1855; services as a cooper; and purchase and sale of farm products.</p>
    </scopecontent>
